The biological activity of the subject human IFN-α's may be an antiviral activity. In one embodiment, the anti-human IFN-∀ monoclonal antibody is capable of binding to and neutralizing the antiviral activity of all, or substantially all human IFN-α subtypes. In another embodiment, the anti-human IFN-∀ monoclonal antibody is capable of binding to and neutralizing the antiviral activity of each of human IFN-∀ 





subtypes





