The ability of a candidate antibody to neutralize the antiviral activity of IFN-α was assayed as described by 
Yousefi, S., et al., Am. J. Clin. Pathol., 83: 735-740 (1985
). Briefly, the assay was performed using human lung carcinoma A549 cells challenged with encephalomyocarditis (EMC) virus. Serial dilutions of mAbs were incubated with various units of type I interferons for one hour at 37EC in a total volume of 100 :1. These mixtures were then incubated with 5x10
5
 A549 cells in 100 :1 of cell culture medium for 24 hours. Cells were then challenged with 2x10
5
